  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Scheduled for elective primary total knee replacement surgery

          -  Legal minimum age requirement ( country-specific)

          -  Written informed consent has been obtained

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Documented history or considered to be at increased risk of venous thromboembolism

          -  Subjects considered to be at increased risk of bleeding:

               -  Known hemorrhagic disorder and/or coagulation disorder

               -  Thrombocytopenia

               -  Clinically important bleeding occurred within 3 months prior to the screening
                  visit

          -  Acute bacterial endocarditis

          -  Severe hypertension

          -  Retinopathy

          -  Concomitant use of anticoagulants / antiplatelet agents (including homeopathic drugs)
             and/or anticipated postoperative need for other reasons than prevention of DVT during
             the study period.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
